CHAPTER ONE: THE INVITATION<br>
<br>
A smoky haze filled the Hogcaller's Inn, hiding the grimy interior and its equally grimy occupants. The audience was transfixed on the half-elven bard who crooned a sweet melody, all being grateful that something beautiful could happen to this hell-hole. Even Swin Blackeye, the barkeep, fell under her spell and was not spouting his usual colorful insults at the customers. <br>
<br>
As the last note hung in the air, Lady Robyn Sheyoshke smiled at her ragtag, flea ridden spectators with genuine warmth. She actually was able to bring a spark of happiness to these poor wretches. Sumlain, her companion in arms and travel, started clapping loudly. The patrons all joined in with gusto, stomping their feet until the very timbers of the tavern threatened to collapse.<br>
<br>
As Robyn joined Sumlain for a drink at the table, a young street urchin rushed up to her. He had a message from Tyber Mizis (/ooc if you haven't already done so, you should ask him what that last name means - very fitting!). As Robyn tipped the grubby little boy, she wondered what her old roguish friend would be sending her. The parchment indicated that Tyber's guild, The Sanguine Blade, was having a gathering at Solusek's Eye, a nasty place for the uninitiated. The leaders wanted to introduce the younglings to the dungeon, as well as -uh- &quot;acquire&quot; items of interest to the guild. Tyber thought Robyn and Sumlain would like to join the fun and bloodshed.<br>
<br>
Robyn and Sumlain decided that any trouble Tyber could stir up could be nothing but amusing. As the two adventurers headed for the door, a drunk barbarian decided that Robyn needed to sing him a personal song in his room. Before she could cut him down with her sharp tongue (and her sharp sword), Sumlain slammed him against the wall, told him to be a gentleman, and to mind his manners around his lady. Robyn sighed and walked out into the night, mumbling about too much testosterone giving her a headache. <br>
<br>
Robyn Sheyoshke<br>
25th level Warbler <br>
